"a.明晰的；明瞭的 【英】 adj. 明晰的；明瞭的(clea rly expressed or presented) 【考】 反义词：opacity(难 懂); dull(呆滞的)-perspi cuous(明瞭的) 【同】 派生词：perspicuity n. 明白 无 【记】per 透过,通过 + spic spect 看,很透明能够看的清楚的；perspicacious结尾是ca，音：才，有才气的人独具慧眼，指人，perspicuous指物，如文章 【相关】conspicuous (con + spect 大家都能看到的→显著的), per 透过,通过 + spic spect 看,能透过现象看本质的→敏锐, suspicion (sus + pect 底下看→怀疑) perspicuous (adj.)  late 15c., from Latin perspicuus ""transparent, clear, evident,"" from perspicere ""look through, look closely at"" (see perspective). Related: Perspicuously; perspicuousness."
